Install mysqldb module for python by typing :sudo apt-get install python-MySQLdb
Open mysql via terminal and create a database (preferably use the name varnan).Inside this database create a table reports with the following description:
+-------------+-----------+------+-----+-------------------+----------------+
| Field       | Type      | Null | Key | Default           | Extra          |
+-------------+-----------+------+-----+-------------------+----------------+
| ID          | int(11)   | NO   | PRI | NULL              | auto_increment |
| DESCRIPTION | text      | NO   |     | NULL              |                |
| GPS         | char(200) | YES  |     | NULL              |                |
| USERID      | char(150) | YES  |     | NULL              |                |
| STATUS      | char(60)  | YES  |     | NULL              |                |
| FORWARDEDTO | char(120) | YES  |     | NULL              |                |
| DATETIMEID  | timestamp | NO   |     | CURRENT_TIMESTAMP |                |
+-------------+-----------+------+-----+-------------------+----------------+
Change the value of the username,database and password in the file database.py to the configuration that suits your system.
Start the upload script by typing : python upload.py 
Start the task allocation script by typing: python allocate.py
Start the ftp server by going in the images folder(cd images) and type: python -m SimpleHTTPServer 8070
